review_blob:
Light yellow and murky - nice white head. A strange off-smell - maybe its the strawberry pur? Some nice fruity and hoppy notes though. Dont pick up much vanilla.

Thick mouthfeel - hoppy and fruity but once again it suffers under the odd strawberry flavor.

Either this beer is intensely over rated or just a bad batch.
beer_name: Tired Hands / Omnipollo Milkshake IPA - Strawberry

review_blob: Beautiful murky light yellow color. Longlasting white head. Not as "in your face" as other Omnipollo IPAs but still nice and refreshing. Piney, grassy and citric.

Beautiful dark murky beer with a longlasting white head. Really sharp and tart aroma - notes of white grape and some tropical fruit.
Taste is equallysour and refreshing with some classic Nelson notes of goose berry and white grape.
Very drinkable and refreshing although quite sour and bitter.
Interesting, sour and just slightly smokey aroma with a bit of hops as well. I dont pick up much smoke tastewise (unfortunately) but it is nice, tart and refreshing.
Nice hoppy aroma with notes of tropical fruit and citrus. Same notes tastewise but with a strong and roasted coffee backbone.
Decent beer, not as coffe forward as expected. It has a nice bitter coffee roast though and its pleasantly followed through by notes of chocolate and some grassy hops.
Deep dark fruity aroma with a nice roasted note. Deep, roasy and very sweet taste. Very enjoyable.
beer_name: Evil Twin I Love You With My Stout

review_blob: Relatively disapointing beer. Spicy, sweet and boozy notes but all in all a bit too faint.
Great imperial stout. Good ballance between sweet and roasted notes. Coffee, chocolate and a relatively thick and creamy mouth feel

Aroma has an interesting has an interesting mix of roasted notes, coffee, chocolate and a delicious note. Mouthfeel is a bit thin and the taste sensations are not as strong as the aroma - citric and roasted though
beer_name: Mikkeller Orange Yuzu Glad I Said Porter

review_blob: Good stuff. Surprisingly hoppy and citric in the beginning but followed up by a sweet, boozy barley wine sensation. Surprisingly good.

Great aroma: citric hops, rhubarb, vanilla and maybe a bit of fresh tart strarberry
Taste: Very refreshing, citric and hoppy. Some notes of vanilla
beer_name: Omnipollo Magic #411 - Wild Strawberry/Rhubarb/Vanilla Smoothie IPA

review_blob: Pretty decent pale ale. Nice peachy aroma. Tastewise it is dry, pleasantly hoppy and a bit flat.
Pitch black and beautiful. Fizzy head though. Absolutely Wonderful aroma - sweet and dark fruity, rasinins and smoke, vanilla and chocolate. Roasted, smoked and sweet Taste.

Murky orange beer, long lasting head. Very nice, peachy, tropical, juicy aroma. Tastewise it is nice and refreshing but not as interesting as the aroma. A bit faint. Quite dry but not very bitter. Would be nice on a hot summer day.

Rarely do I taste something truely original and succesfull at the same time - this is an exception. Amazing and spicy aroma of sweet rice, cinamon and tons of vanilla. Tastewise it is a bit more subtle but nonetheless a true spice bomb. Would be lovely with a portion of Danish risalamande.
Amazing aroma of gentle coffee. Notes of coffee, vanilla, caramel, bourbon. Unfortunately it has no carbonation what so ever which destroys the first hand impression
Nice hoppy, citric and floral taste and aroma but with clear burnt and roasted notes. A slight taste of coffee

Wonderful dark beer with roasted notes of coffee, rye, licorice and some sweet (nearly cakey) and slightly smokey sensation. Best beer ive had from Beer Here, and one of the best Danish beers ive had in a while.
Very very decent ipa. Loads of hoppy tropical notes and some some citrus. Nice malt backbone as well.
Not the best amager beer, but deffinately very drinkable. Crisp and citric.
Quite alright ipa with clear spicy notes of ginger and pine, just as promised.
Great IPA with a relatively strong malt backbone. Both aroma and tastewise the dominant factor is citrus though. A bit of peach and a long bitter aftertaste. Nice.

Ridiculously underrated beer. Beautiful murky red color frem the added cheries and aroma of both tropical hops, tart cherries and sour yeast. Taste is pleasantly sour with strong notes of cheries and citric hops.

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: Not as good as "dank & sticky" partly due to the fact that is seems slightly boozy. It is still a nice beer though with notes of especially citrus (!). So in that sense it is exactly what the bottle is promising.

Very nice hoppy and fruity aroma with clear notes of citrus, tangerine, orange and passion fruit and other tropical fruits. Tastewise it has equal qualities but it has an unfortunate off-flavor that destroys it a bit
beer_name: Amager / Beerbliotek International Men of Mystery

review_blob: Hazy lightly yellow color, small white head. Very pleasant citric and orangy aroma with notes of tangerine, passion fruit and pineapple. Nice and bitter taste impression - loads of citrus and lemon notes with some tropical fruit

Finally a Brewdog beer that actually really hits the nail. Sweet and cakey notes with undertones of roastiness and pleasant alcohol. Some sweet dark fruit as well. aromawise it is not overwhelming - a bit boozy - still pretty nice though.

Very decent imperial stout, but calling it "Cocoa Psycho" is simply just a joke and yet another exaggeration from Brewdog. It seems like this brewery just never really pulls it off. But, as said, this is a very decent imperial stout. Pitch black, nice, longlasting roasted head. Aroma: some chocolate, coffee, roasted notes, soap. Taste: A bit of cakey choclotate, bitter coffee, burnt malt.

Not the promised amount of tropical fruit - nonetheless its yet another good IPA fro Ugly duck. Bitter citrus, pine and grassy notes domintates. Long aftertaste. Nice hazy color.

A bit of Mango when it gets warmer
beer_name: Ugly Duck Paps In The Tropics

review_blob: Meaty and smokey aroma with notes of especially chocolate. Taste is equally smokey, somewhat subtle though, with notes of chocolate, coffee and a quite dry finish.
Murky and fizzy yellow color, very nice aroma of sweet citric and tropical mosaic - Something Funky as well. Taste is Funky, tart, hoppy, fruity, refreshing and very enjoyable.
Very very interesting and enjoyable ipa. Citrus, grape fruits, tea leafs, exotic fruit, pineapple, peach.
Bitter and citric with a strong and sweet malt backbone. Not the most interesting Stone beer if you ask me.
Decent but not overwhelming. Refreshing ipa character, but nothing extraordinary.
Booze, chocolate, coffee, dark fruit, coffee -chocolate. Thick and nice. Pretty nice
Decent stuff - bitter and refreshing. Some fruity, citric and enjoyable hoppy notes. A bit over rated - still pretty good though. After all Stone never fails.
Crisp, refreshing and juicy, but not too complex. Some bitter, grassy, piney, fruity and citric notes.
Strong notes of spicy tobaco, honey and ripe fruit. Some hoppy character as well. Quite interesting and enjoyable.
Amazing beer that gives room to both the coffee, vanilla, chocolate and the, subtle, chili. What a beer.
Decent ipa, but nonetheless annother "just alright " beer from rogue. Bitter, piney and somewhat grape fruity.
beer_name: Rogue Nation Brutal India Pale Ale

review_blob: Pitch black, not much head. Aroma of liqorice, coffee, dark chocolate, dark fruit and some booze. Taste is roasted and Slightly sweet with notes of coffee, chocolate, liqorice. Good stuff.

A sweet and barly like sensation hits you In the face when you first taste this beer. A sticky and pungent hop bittwrness follows. All in All it makes up for an interesting beer. Fun to try, but probably not your new favourite.
Corn like and sweet aroma. Taste is ballanced between tart and sweet fruit and salty wheat notes. Not too familiar with this style yet, but it seems to be pretty decent without being overwhelming.

Bitter and hoppy ipa with notes of both grape fruit, pine and Something more fruity. Combined with the sweet, spicy and sticky tripel sensation it makes up for quite an interesting beer. I do believe i sence the red wine barrels when the beer gets a bit warmer as well.
beer_name: Stone / Ecliptic / Wicked Weed Points Unknown IPA

review_blob: Fizzy yellow color, massive white head. Interesting sweet and bitter aroma. Tastewise it has a sharp citric note without ever becoming too complex. Not brilliant, but not that bad either.
beer_name: Twisted Pine Farm to Foam Series Roots Revival

review_blob: This was a decent surprise for me - really nice ipa! Citric notes of sweet grape fruit, orange and tangerine combined with some tropical fruit and peach. Both refreshing and complex.

Pitch black with a nice dark roasted head. Sweet and roasted aroma with fudgy notes of coffee, chocolate, and dried fruit. Taste is dominated by chocolate, coffee, some liqorice, sugar, booze and a thick nearly cakey feel.
beer_name: Evil Twin An Ms a Jess

review_blob: Quite crisp and refreshing pilsner character. Other than that nothing special.
Sweet and caramellized malt aroma. Same could be said about the taste although it is backed up by a slight metallic note. Quite refreshing though. No trace of the promised smoke.
beer_name: Four Peaks Kilt Lifter Scottish Style Ale
